subSubSection.paragraph:
It differs from a number of nominal taxa currently synonymised with
C. robustus
in the combination of more greatly expanded toe and finger discs (all synonyms), presence of distinct terminal groove on the first finger and absence of light flecks on the thighs and lateral surfaces (vs
C. microtis
), absence of yellow flecks and pigmentation across the body (vs
Pomatops valvifera
), in having a truncate (vs rounded) snout tip and smaller size ( 42– 49mm vs 54.6mm ) (vs
Liophyrne kampeni
) (
Zweifel 1972
,
Kraus and Allison 2009
).
